  "notes": "Per-hole pars, stroke indexes and meters come from the RFEG club microsite (ClubId=670) and were cross-checked against the club's official website scorecard at newsierragolf.com — all 72 per-hole distances and all pars match exactly. Internal consistency verified: pars sum to 72 (36 out / 36 in), stroke indexes form a permutation of 1-18, and each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to the published totals (Blancas 6818 m, Amarillas 6261 m, Azules 5756 m, Rojas 5579 m). RFEG 9-hole rating splits for men: Blancas 37.5/132 + 38.5/134; Amarillas 35.7/133 + 37.3/126; Azules 34.2/127 + 35.8/129; Rojas 33.5/120 + 35.4/128. Women's ratings (Vc/Vs) come from the RFEG club listing page (id=555, Club Sierra Golf — same facility, Carretera Hacienda del Escobar 1, Balsicas), which rates all four tees for both genders; its men's values match the microsite's 18-hole totals exactly, so the women's figures are taken as the current 18-hole ratings. Minor discrepancy: the club website's HCP column rendered noisily in extraction (e.g. hole 1 showed 5 vs RFEG 4, hole 18 duplicated 5); the RFEG stroke-index allocation (identical across all tees) is used as authoritative. golfify.io, mscorecard.com and 1golf.eu returned 403 and could not be used as additional cross-checks. Note the Blancas card is very long (6818 m); this is as published by RFEG for the expanded 18-hole layout."
